<subSubSection id="C33665450037FFE4FF6CFC30FDA15DE5" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0037FFE7FF6CFC30FB4D5BAF" blockId="1.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FF6CFC30FEF95CAB" bold="true" box="[151,267,973,999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FEEAFC33FE6B5CA4" author="Lane, F." box="[273,409,973,1000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref6248" refString="Lane, F. (1956) Cerambycoidea Neotropica nova IV (Coleoptera). Dusenia, 7 (1), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1956">Lane (1956)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FDEBFC33FD9B5CAB" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[528,617,974,999]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FDEBFC33FD9B5CAB" box="[528,617,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FC61FC33FB665CA4" authority="Lane, 1956" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[922,1172,973,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FC61FC33FBFD5CAB" box="[922,1039,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FBEEFC33FB665CA4" author="Lane, F." box="[1045,1172,973,1000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref6248" refString="Lane, F. (1956) Cerambycoidea Neotropica nova IV (Coleoptera). Dusenia, 7 (1), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1956">Lane, 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as follows (translated): “Close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FEF2FC0CFE005B47" authority="Latr., 1829" authorityName="Latr." authorityYear="1829" box="[265,498,1009,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FEF2FC0CFE9F5B47" box="[265,365,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Adesmus</emphasis>
Latr., 1829
</taxonomicName>
, from which differs by the following features: head with the frons concave, shieldshaped, inferiorly ending in acute apex, split at the end and projected out; antennae 12-segmented; the third about 1.5 times longer than the scape; fourth shorter than third and longer than the scape; the others gradually shorter, the last ones subequal in length; elytra strongly projected at apices and ending in acute spine; the sutural angles rounded; mesoventral process wider; pro- and mesotarsomere I about as long as the third, in the metatarsomere I slightly longer.” In the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FDC4FB5BFD445BF3" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[575,694,1190,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FDC4FB5BFD445BF3" box="[575,694,1190,1215]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he only commented about the scape (translated): “… scape long, very slightly and gradually widened toward the apex, which is truncate with shiny apical ring.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0037FFE7FF3CFB10FE125AF7" blockId="1.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FF3CFB10FE195A4B" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[199,491,1261,1287]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="575 - 579" refId="ref6317" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1992) Generos de Hemilophini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) com antenas de doze articulos. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 36 (3), 575 - 579." type="journal article" year="1992">Martins &amp; Galileo (1992)</bibRefCitation>
provided the first key to species of Hemilophini with 12-segmented antennae. The shape of the scape was not used as a differential feature. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FC60FAECFB455A67" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[923,1207,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1868" refId="ref6425" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte I. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Volume 13. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 3 - 231." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
the scape in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FABFFAEFFA6F5A67" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[1348,1437,1298,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FABFFAEFFA6F5A67" box="[1348,1437,1298,1323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has apical cicatrix. In fact, the scape of the 
<typeStatus id="5497886C0037FFE7FD89FAC8FD265A03" box="[626,724,1333,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FCCFFACBFC5B5A03" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[820,937,1334,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FCCFFACBFC5B5A03" box="[820,937,1334,1359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0037FFE7FC4CFAC8FBEC5A03" box="[951,1054,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956, holotype male: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Elytral carinae; 5) Head, frontal view; 6) Head, lateral view; 7) Scape, apical cicatrix; 8) Scape, detail. 9–11) Purusia acreana, female: 9) Head, lateral view; 10) Dorsal habitus; 11) Ventral habitus. 12) Purusiella wappesi (Martins &amp; Galileo, 2004), scape. Figure 12 by Francisco Eriberto de Lima Nascimento (MZSP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581638/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
) has a very narrow apical cicatrix. However, it is practically absent in a second male and a female belonging to the MZSP collection. The presence or absence of the apical cicatrix on the scape was used in the key to genera by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FC24FA80FB0D5ADB" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[991,1279,1405,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1868" refId="ref6425" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte I. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Volume 13. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 3 - 231." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, and followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FF41FA5CFE2E5AF7" author="Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Heffern, D. &amp; Botero, J. P. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L." box="[186,476,1441,1467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref6750" refString="Santos-Silva, A., Heffern, D., Botero, J. P. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L. (2020) Notes, new records, new combinations, a new genus and three new species in Hemilophini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae: Lamiinae). Insecta Mundi, 785, 1 - 25" type="journal article" year="2020">
Santos-Silva 
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FEB4FA5FFE755AF7" box="[335,391,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0037FFE7FF3CFA38FAEC58C3" blockId="1.[151,1437,973,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FEC0FA38FD965A93" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[315,612,1477,1503]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1868" refId="ref6425" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte I. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Volume 13. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 3 - 231." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
had provided, for the first time, some information about females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FA73FA3BFF00594F" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FA73FA3BFF00594F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(frons convex, without projections; distance between upper eye lobes slightly greater than the width of one lobe), it was never illustrated. Currently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FD8AF9F3FD1B596B" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[625,745,1550,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FD8AF9F3FD1B596B" box="[625,745,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FC41F9F0FBC4596B" box="[954,1078,1549,1575]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FBBCF9F0FB3A596B" box="[1095,1224,1549,1575]" country="Costa Rica" name="Puntarenas" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Puntarenas</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FB26F9F0FACE596B" box="[1245,1340,1549,1575]" name="Ecuador" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FAB1F9F0FA6E596B" box="[1354,1436,1549,1575]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FF64F9CCFEED5907" box="[159,287,1585,1611]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
), and 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FE9AF9CCFE575907" box="[353,421,1585,1611]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FE4FF9CCFE1D5907" box="[436,495,1585,1611]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Acre</collectingRegion>
, Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FD80F9CCFD425907" box="[635,688,1585,1611]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FD41F9CCFCDE5900" box="[698,812,1585,1612]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
). There is no doubt that the species, originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FF2FF9A8FEEA5923" box="[212,280,1621,1647]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FEDDF9A8FEAC5923" box="[294,350,1621,1647]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Acre</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FE68F9A8FE3B5923" box="[403,457,1621,1647]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Pará</collectingRegion>
), really occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FD76F9A8FD2D5923" box="[653,735,1621,1647]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FCEFF9A8FC835923" box="[788,881,1621,1647]" name="Ecuador" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
because we have examined specimens from these countries, personally or through photographs. The occurrence in the Brazilian state of Rondônia and in 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FAF6F987FAB259D8" box="[1293,1344,1658,1684]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Peru</collectingCountry>
is probable (the occurrence in 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F82C0037FFE7FE63F963FDFC59F4" box="[408,526,1694,1720]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
is confirmed herein). Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FC51F960FB3759FB" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[938,1221,1693,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="575 - 579" refId="ref6317" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1992) Generos de Hemilophini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) com antenas de doze articulos. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 36 (3), 575 - 579." type="journal article" year="1992">Martins &amp; Galileo (1992)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide the name of the collection where the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FD3FF93FFD055990" box="[708,759,1730,1756]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Peru</collectingCountry>
was deposited. In the same way, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FB8EF93CFA6E5997" author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F." box="[1141,1436,1729,1755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" refId="ref6542" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F. (1994) Checklist of the Cerambycidae and Disteniidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Wolfsgarden Books, Burbank, 409 pp." type="book" year="1994">Monné &amp; Giesbert (1994)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide the name of the institution of the specimen(s) used by them to record the species for the Brazilian state of Rondônia. Therefore, it is not possible to verify the specimen’s identity. This is a recurring problem in many publications where new records are established. However, we know that the specimens used by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FB35F8D0FA6E580B" author="Swift, I. P. &amp; Bezark, L. G. &amp; Nearns, E. H. &amp; Solis, A. &amp; Hovore, F. T." box="[1230,1436,1837,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref6811" refString="Swift, I. P., Bezark, L. G., Nearns, E. H., Solis, A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2010) Checklist of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of Costa Rica. Insecta Mundi, 131, 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010">
Swift 
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FAE9F8D3FAB9580B" box="[1298,1355,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
to record 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FEFAF8AFFE855827" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[257,375,1874,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FEFAF8AFFE855827" box="[257,375,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FE42F8ACFDC75827" box="[441,565,1873,1899]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, in fact, belongs to the new species described here: the specimen used by them is the 
<typeStatus id="5497886C0037FFE7FF21F88BFEC858DC" box="[218,314,1910,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FE9BF88BFDF358C3" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[352,513,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raberi">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FE9BF88BFDF358C3" box="[352,513,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Juninia raberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FD70F88BFCB758C3" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[651,837,1910,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FD70F88BFCB758C3" box="[651,837,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Purusia acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is excluded from the fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="F33B765E0037FFE7FB67F888FAE858C3" box="[1180,1306,1909,1935]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0037FFE4FF3CF864FBE85E51" blockId="1.[151,1437,973,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,150,681]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
The conspicuous frontal shape of the males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FD33F867FCD358FF" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[712,801,1946,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FD33F867FCD358FF" box="[712,801,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allows separating them from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FB3DF867FA6E58FF" authority="Lane, 1966" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1966" box="[1222,1436,1945,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FB3DF867FAE858FF" box="[1222,1306,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Juninia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FADBF867FA6E58FF" author="Lane, F." box="[1312,1436,1945,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="245 - 249" refId="ref6274" refString="Lane, F. (1966) Novos generos e especies de Hemilophini I. Generos com antenas de 12 articulos (Coleoptera, Lamiidae). Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 18 (21), 245 - 249." type="journal article" year="1966">Lane, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FF3CF840FD87589B" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1993" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1993" box="[199,629,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sibapipunga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FF3CF840FEA7589B" box="[199,341,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Sibapipunga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0037FFE7FEA6F840FD87589B" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[349,629,1981,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="109 - 116" refId="ref6365" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1993) Descricao de novos taxons com antenas de doze articulos, transferencia de especies de Adesmus Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1825 e sinonimos (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Hemilophini). Iheringia, Zoologia, 74, 109 - 116." type="journal article" year="1993">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0037FFE7FCFCF843FC92589B" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[775,864,1982,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0037FFE7FCFCF843FC92589B" box="[775,864,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there is a single and strongly conspicuous projection, narrowed and bifid apically (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0034FFE4FDE4FF6AFD7A5FFE" box="[543,648,150,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956, holotype male: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Elytral carinae; 5) Head, frontal view; 6) Head, lateral view; 7) Scape, apical cicatrix; 8) Scape, detail. 9–11) Purusia acreana, female: 9) Head, lateral view; 10) Dorsal habitus; 11) Ventral habitus. 12) Purusiella wappesi (Martins &amp; Galileo, 2004), scape. Figure 12 by Francisco Eriberto de Lima Nascimento (MZSP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581638/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
); males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FCF0FF6AFC6B5FFD" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1993" box="[779,921,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sibapipunga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FCF0FF6AFC6B5FFD" box="[779,921,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Sibapipunga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have two nearly conical projections directed forward (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0034FFE4FF05FF46FEA05F99" box="[254,338,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,382,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-136@6.[151,1436,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Sibapipunga beckeri (Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992). 21) Holotype female, dorsal habitus. 22–25) Male: 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Ventral habitus; 24) Lateral habitus; 25) Frontal tubercles. 26) Holotype female, elytral carinae (by Diego de Santana Souza)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581646/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); and males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FE03FF46FDBE5F98" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1966" box="[504,588,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FE03FF46FDBE5F98" box="[504,588,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Juninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have no projections on frons. However, it is not possible to separate females of these three genera. The only feature that is possible to use, provisionally, is the shape of the elytral apex: with long spine at outer apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FE3DFEFEFDED5E50" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[454,543,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FE3DFEFEFDED5E50" box="[454,543,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, short in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FD72FEFEFD2F5E50" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1966" box="[649,733,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FD72FEFEFD2F5E50" box="[649,733,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Juninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FC7DFEFEFBE65E51" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1993" box="[902,1044,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sibapipunga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FC7DFEFEFBE65E51" box="[902,1044,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Sibapipunga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0034FFE4FF3CFEDAFC915E9D" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
In the key to genera from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B3F0034FFE4FE0DFEDAFCEF5E0D" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[502,797,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="1868" refId="ref6425" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte I. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Volume 13. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 3 - 231." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FCD1FEDAFC715E0C" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[810,899,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FCD1FEDAFC715E0C" box="[810,899,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FC46FEDAFF3D5E29" authority="Dalens, Touroult &amp; Tavakilian, 2010" authorityName="Dalens, Touroult &amp; Tavakilian" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FC46FEDAFBC05E0D" box="[957,1074,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Purusiella</emphasis>
Dalens, Touroult &amp; Tavakilian, 2010
</taxonomicName>
were separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FE32FEB6FDEF5E28" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1966" box="[457,541,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FE32FEB6FDEF5E28" box="[457,541,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Juninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FDADFEB6FD165E29" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1993" box="[598,740,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sibapipunga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FDADFEB6FD165E29" box="[598,740,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Sibapipunga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an apical cicatrix on the scape in the two former genera, which is absent in the last two. In fact, the apical cicatrix in the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FB5BFE92FAE75EC5" authorityName="Dalens, Touroult &amp; Tavakilian" authorityYear="2010" box="[1184,1301,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FB5BFE92FAE75EC5" box="[1184,1301,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Purusiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0034FFE4FADDFE92FA8B5EC5" box="[1318,1401,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956, holotype male: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Elytral carinae; 5) Head, frontal view; 6) Head, lateral view; 7) Scape, apical cicatrix; 8) Scape, detail. 9–11) Purusia acreana, female: 9) Head, lateral view; 10) Dorsal habitus; 11) Ventral habitus. 12) Purusiella wappesi (Martins &amp; Galileo, 2004), scape. Figure 12 by Francisco Eriberto de Lima Nascimento (MZSP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581638/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) is strongly conspicuous. However, as it is slightly conspicuous or nearly absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FBD6FE6EFB745EE0" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[1069,1158,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FBD6FE6EFB745EE0" box="[1069,1158,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Purusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a new key to genera of Hemilophini with antennae 12-segmented needs to be provided.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0034FFE4FF3CFE26FCBD5D55" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
The tarsal claws in male (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0034FFE4FE0BFE26FDB15EB9" box="[496,579,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1137,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-420@7.[151,1436,1137,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Protarsal claws. 27–28) Sibapipunga beckeri (Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992): 27) Holotype female (by Diego de Santana Souza); 28) Male. 29–30) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956: 29) Holotype male; 30) Female. 31–32) Juninia annulifera (Kirsch, 1889): 31) Female; 32) Juninia leechi Lane, 1966, paratype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581648/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) and female (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B0034FFE4FD18FE26FCC45EB9" box="[739,822,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1137,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-420@7.[151,1436,1137,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Protarsal claws. 27–28) Sibapipunga beckeri (Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992): 27) Holotype female (by Diego de Santana Souza); 28) Male. 29–30) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956: 29) Holotype male; 30) Female. 31–32) Juninia annulifera (Kirsch, 1889): 31) Female; 32) Juninia leechi Lane, 1966, paratype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581648/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D0034FFE4FC93FE26FC125EB8" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1956" box="[872,992,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Purusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acreana">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FC93FE26FC125EB8" box="[872,992,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">P. acreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar: the inner tooth is not noticeably widened basally and is shorter than the outer tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336CE0034FFE4FF3CFDDFFDA15DE5" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B958EADC0034FFE4FF3CFDDFFD955D70" bold="true" box="[199,615,546,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
